<paragraph id="FF6FB4B0737A34AA71749920B861F7FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6914FF9981E7CCB3401FCC9BCA3F458" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AEE2944E47915EE4A4AE48867E9FC4E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="173DBB59B25B3654B81195CFA3CB6B31" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The species 
<taxonomicName id="B5352A03637F3E0CA4E7470FC894E569" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia sourakovi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sourakovi">
<emphasis id="E3F3D7B41740077350DAA3AF480BAE08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia sourakovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in a deciduous forest at 1800 m elevation in southeastern Peru (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BAC5D25C4F84BC09C29068263188AD55" captionStart="Figure 93" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 93. Distribution of examined specimens of the genera Gaujonia and Gaujoptera." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.985.51622.figure93" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471615" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">93</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
